SIMPLE: wearisome
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wearisome
<hw>Wea"ri*some</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Causing weariness;
tiresome; tedious; weariful; <as>as, a <ex>wearisome</ex> march; a
<ex>wearisome</ex> day's work; a <ex>wearisome</ex> book</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These high wild hills and rough uneven ways⟦br⟧
Draws out our miles, and makes them <qex>wearisome</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Irksome; tiresome; tedious; fatiguing; annoying;
vexatious. See <er>Irksome</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Wea"ri*some*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Wea"ri*some*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weary</ent>⟦br⟧
